            <h4 data-uuid="46dbac5bf71549bdbaf0392e93e96f46">Section 3. Treason</h4>
            <ol data-uuid="b3297caae8874fdfa19e2ab38ea12d92">
                <li data-uuid="2154202b940e4da3a13e0b8dfcef42e6"><b>Definition Treason</b> against the United States, shall consist only in levying War against them, or in adhering to their Enemies, giving them Aid and Comfort. No Person shall be convicted of Treason unless on the Testimony of two Witnesses to the same overt Act, or on Confession in open Court.</li>
                <li data-uuid="b93f42aacb8a4a62a748567538befcfc"><b>Punishment</b>
                    The Congress shall have Power to declare the Punishment of Treason, but no
                    Attainder of Treason shall work <a href="[remark:60ca89f117ae40a28e963d3fa662447e]"> Corruption of Blood</a>, or Forfeiture
                    except during the Life of the Person attainted.<br />
                </li>
            </ol>
